description.narrative: More than 1,600;children were provided with mental health and psychosocial support;through;remote technologies amidst;national;closures;and;a protracted;state of emergency;due to the COVID-19 pandemic.;In 2021,;further;strides were made in the integration of;the;migrant response into;development efforts;including;strengthening;foster care;systems,;development of;child protection information management systems and;bi-lingual;communication of policies and;other advocacy and;awareness-raising tools.;With UNICEF’s;support,;prevention of sexual abuse and exploitation;standards and measures to safeguard children were strengthened among implementing partners;and;over 600;children benefitted from;efforts to mitigate;gender-based;violence.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2022
